criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Having a level of trait anxiety [Spielberger State-Trait Anxiety Inventory (Form
             Y1)]{23642} that was ≥ the 75th percentile for their age (i.e., ≥ 46 and ≥ 44 for
             women and men, respectively)

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Current treatment for anxiety or depression;

          -  History of bipolar disorder, mania, or psychotic disorders;

          -  History of winter depression, which might bias towards positive response to light;

          -  Hypertension;

          -  Ophthalmic abnormalities; and

          -  Usual exposure to high levels of light such that the intervention would add little to
             usual exposure.
